        <date>1899</date>
        <persName>
          <forename>Dimitar Anastasov</forename>
          <surname>Karastoyanov</surname>
          <ref target="info:fedora/context:vase.pn.c700660e" type="context">Karastoyanov, Dimitar Anastasov</ref>
        </persName>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Full length shot of a group of eight men, seven of them in formal suits, one in military uniform; all with insignia of honour. Six of the men are seated in the first row around a covered table. A man in military uniform and a man in plain city clothes are standing left and right behind a seated man in the center. A painted canvas backdrop is creating the illusion of the scene being set in a lounge.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Members of the Cabinet with Prime Minister Konstantin Stoilov (1853 – 1901), who was a leading Bulgarian politician and twice Prime Minister of the Principality of Bulgaria. His first reign as Prime Minister lasted only for a brief spell in 1887. His second mandate was 1894 - 1899.</ab>
